lead_paragraph: A new roof was all the rage when the U.S. Open began two weeks ago but it was the crowning of a new world number one and two first-time champions that left their mark on a tournament that came to an emotional close on Sunday with a tribute to victims of the Sept. 11, 2001 attacks.

headline.print_headline: New Champions Add to Fresh Look of U.S. Open
headline.main: New Champions Add to Fresh Look of U.S. Open
